7 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
8 // ----
9 // This pass forwards branches to unconditional branches to make them branch ----
10 // directly to the target block. This pass often results in dead MBB's, which ----
11 // it then removes. ----
12 // ----
13 // Note that this pass must be run after register allocation, it cannot handle ----
14 // SSA form. It also must handle virtual registers for targets that emit virtual ----
15 // ISA (e.g. NVPTX). ----
16 // ----
17 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
18 ----

158 void BranchFolder::RemoveDeadBlock(MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
159 assert(MBB->pred_empty() && "MBB must be dead!"); 0
160 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nRemoving MBB: " << *MBB); 0
161 ----
162 MachineFunction *MF = MBB->getParent(); 0
163 // drop all successors. ----
164 while (!MBB->succ_empty()) 0
165 MBB->removeSuccessor(MBB->succ_end()-1); 0
166 ----
167 // Avoid matching if this pointer gets reused. ----
168 TriedMerging.erase(MBB); 0
169 ----
170 // Update call site info. ----
171 for (const MachineInstr &MI : *MBB) 0
172 if (MI.shouldUpdateCallSiteInfo()) 0
173 MF->eraseCallSiteInfo(&MI); 0
174 ----
175 // Remove the block. ----
176 MF->erase(MBB); 0
177 EHScopeMembership.erase(MBB); 0
178 if (MLI) 0
179 MLI->removeBlock(MBB); 0
180 } 0

182 bool BranchFolder::OptimizeFunction(MachineFunction &MF, 0
183 const TargetInstrInfo *tii, ----
184 const TargetRegisterInfo *tri, ----
185 MachineLoopInfo *mli, bool AfterPlacement) { ----
186 if (!tii) return false; 0
187 ----
188 TriedMerging.clear(); 0
189 ----
190 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo(); 0
191 AfterBlockPlacement = AfterPlacement; 0
192 TII = tii; 0
193 TRI = tri; 0
194 MLI = mli; 0
195 this->MRI = &MRI; 0
196 ----
197 UpdateLiveIns = MRI.tracksLiveness() && TRI->trackLivenessAfterRegAlloc(MF); 0
198 if (!UpdateLiveIns) 0
199 MRI.invalidateLiveness(); 0
200 ----
201 bool MadeChange = false; 0
202 ----
203 // Recalculate EH scope membership. ----
204 EHScopeMembership = getEHScopeMembership(MF); 0
205 ----
206 bool MadeChangeThisIteration = true; 0
207 while (MadeChangeThisIteration) { 0
208 MadeChangeThisIteration = TailMergeBlocks(MF); 0
209 // No need to clean up if tail merging does not change anything after the ----
210 // block placement. ----
211 if (!AfterBlockPlacement || MadeChangeThisIteration) 0
212 MadeChangeThisIteration |= OptimizeBranches(MF); 0
213 if (EnableHoistCommonCode) 0
214 MadeChangeThisIteration |= HoistCommonCode(MF); 0
215 MadeChange |= MadeChangeThisIteration; 0
216 } ----
217 ----
218 // See if any jump tables have become dead as the code generator ----
219 // did its thing. ----
220 MachineJumpTableInfo *JTI = MF.getJumpTableInfo(); 0
221 if (!JTI) 0
222 return MadeChange; 0
223 ----
224 // Walk the function to find jump tables that are live. ----
225 BitVector JTIsLive(JTI->getJumpTables().size()); 0
226 for (const MachineBasicBlock &BB : MF) { 0
227 for (const MachineInstr &I : BB) 0
228 for (const MachineOperand &Op : I.operands()) { 0
229 if (!Op.isJTI()) continue; 0
230 ----
231 // Remember that this JT is live. ----
232 JTIsLive.set(Op.getIndex()); 0
233 } ----
234 } ----
235 ----
236 // Finally, remove dead jump tables. This happens when the ----
237 // indirect jump was unreachable (and thus deleted). ----
238 for (unsigned i = 0, e = JTIsLive.size(); i != e; ++i) 0
239 if (!JTIsLive.test(i)) { 0
240 JTI->RemoveJumpTable(i); 0
241 MadeChange = true; 0
242 } ----
243 ----
244 return MadeChange; 0
245 } 0

251 /// HashMachineInstr - Compute a hash value for MI and its operands. ----
252 static unsigned HashMachineInstr(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
253 unsigned Hash = MI.getOpcode(); 0
254 for (unsigned i = 0, e = MI.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
255 const MachineOperand &Op = MI.getOperand(i); 0
256 ----
257 // Merge in bits from the operand if easy. We can't use MachineOperand's ----
258 // hash_code here because it's not deterministic and we sort by hash value ----
259 // later. ----
260 unsigned OperandHash = 0; 0
261 switch (Op.getType()) { 0
262 case MachineOperand::MO_Register: 0
263 OperandHash = Op.getReg(); 0
264 break; 0
265 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: 0
266 OperandHash = Op.getImm(); 0
267 break; 0
268 case MachineOperand::MO_MachineBasicBlock: 0
269 OperandHash = Op.getMBB()->getNumber(); 0
270 break; 0
271 case MachineOperand::MO_FrameIndex: 0
272 case MachineOperand::MO_ConstantPoolIndex: ----
273 case MachineOperand::MO_JumpTableIndex: ----
274 OperandHash = Op.getIndex(); 0
275 break; 0
276 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress: 0
277 case MachineOperand::MO_ExternalSymbol: ----
278 // Global address / external symbol are too hard, don't bother, but do ----
279 // pull in the offset. ----
280 OperandHash = Op.getOffset(); 0
281 break; 0
282 default: 0
283 break; 0
284 } ----
285 ----
286 Hash += ((OperandHash << 3) | Op.getType()) << (i & 31); 0
287 } ----
288 return Hash; 0
289 } ----

294 if (I == MBB.end()) 0
295 return 0; 0

297 return HashMachineInstr(*I); 0

300 /// Whether MI should be counted as an instruction when calculating common tail. ----
301 static bool countsAsInstruction(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
302 return !(MI.isDebugInstr() || MI.isCFIInstruction()); 0
303 } ----
304 ----
305 /// Iterate backwards from the given iterator \p I, towards the beginning of the ----
306 /// block. If a MI satisfying 'countsAsInstruction' is found, return an iterator ----
307 /// pointing to that MI. If no such MI is found, return the end iterator. ----
308 static MachineBasicBlock::iterator ----
309 skipBackwardPastNonInstructions(MachineBasicBlock::iterator I, 0
310 MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { ----
311 while (I != MBB->begin()) { 0
312 --I; 0
313 if (countsAsInstruction(*I)) 0
314 return I; 0
315 } ----
316 return MBB->end(); 0
317 } ----
318 ----
319 /// Given two machine basic blocks, return the number of instructions they ----
320 /// actually have in common together at their end. If a common tail is found (at ----
321 /// least by one instruction), then iterators for the first shared instruction ----
322 /// in each block are returned as well. ----
323 /// ----
324 /// Non-instructions according to countsAsInstruction are ignored. ----
325 static unsigned ComputeCommonTailLength(MachineBasicBlock *MBB1, 0
326 MachineBasicBlock *MBB2, ----
327 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &I1, ----
328 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &I2) { ----
329 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI1 = MBB1->end(); 0
330 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI2 = MBB2->end(); 0
331 ----
332 unsigned TailLen = 0; 0
333 while (true) { ----
334 MBBI1 = skipBackwardPastNonInstructions(MBBI1, MBB1); 0
335 MBBI2 = skipBackwardPastNonInstructions(MBBI2, MBB2); 0
336 if (MBBI1 == MBB1->end() || MBBI2 == MBB2->end()) 0
337 break; 0
338 if (!MBBI1->isIdenticalTo(*MBBI2) || 0
339 // FIXME: This check is dubious. It's used to get around a problem where ----
340 // people incorrectly expect inline asm directives to remain in the same ----
341 // relative order. This is untenable because normal compiler ----
342 // optimizations (like this one) may reorder and/or merge these ----
343 // directives. ----
344 MBBI1->isInlineAsm()) { 0
345 break; 0
346 } ----
347 if (MBBI1->getFlag(MachineInstr::NoMerge) || 0
348 MBBI2->getFlag(MachineInstr::NoMerge)) 0
349 break; 0
350 ++TailLen; 0
351 I1 = MBBI1; 0
352 I2 = MBBI2; 0
353 } ----
354 ----
355 return TailLen; 0
356 } ----

358 void BranchFolder::replaceTailWithBranchTo(MachineBasicBlock::iterator OldInst, 0
359 MachineBasicBlock &NewDest) { ----
360 if (UpdateLiveIns) { 0
361 // OldInst should always point to an instruction. ----
362 MachineBasicBlock &OldMBB = *OldInst->getParent(); 0
363 LiveRegs.clear(); 0
364 LiveRegs.addLiveOuts(OldMBB); 0
365 // Move backward to the place where will insert the jump. ----
366 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = OldMBB.end(); 0
367 do { ----
368 --I; 0
369 LiveRegs.stepBackward(*I); 0
370 } while (I != OldInst); 0
371 ----
372 // Merging the tails may have switched some undef operand to non-undef ones. ----
373 // Add IMPLICIT_DEFS into OldMBB as necessary to have a definition of the ----
374 // register. ----
375 for (MachineBasicBlock::RegisterMaskPair P : NewDest.liveins()) { 0
376 // We computed the liveins with computeLiveIn earlier and should only see ----
377 // full registers: ----
378 assert(P.LaneMask == LaneBitmask::getAll() && 0
379 "Can only handle full register."); ----
380 MCPhysReg Reg = P.PhysReg; 0
381 if (!LiveRegs.available(*MRI, Reg)) 0
382 continue; 0
383 DebugLoc DL; 0
384 BuildMI(OldMBB, OldInst, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF), Reg); 0
385 } 0
386 } ----
387 ----
388 TII->ReplaceTailWithBranchTo(OldInst, &NewDest); 0
389 ++NumTailMerge; 0
390 } 0

392 MachineBasicBlock *BranchFolder::SplitMBBAt(MachineBasicBlock &CurMBB, 0
393 MachineBasicBlock::iterator BBI1, ----
394 const BasicBlock *BB) { ----
395 if (!TII->isLegalToSplitMBBAt(CurMBB, BBI1)) 0
396 return nullptr; 0
397 ----
398 MachineFunction &MF = *CurMBB.getParent(); 0
399 ----
400 // Create the fall-through block. ----
401 MachineFunction::iterator MBBI = CurMBB.getIterator(); 0
402 MachineBasicBlock *NewMBB = MF.CreateMachineBasicBlock(BB); 0
403 CurMBB.getParent()->insert(++MBBI, NewMBB); 0
404 ----
405 // Move all the successors of this block to the specified block. ----
406 NewMBB->transferSuccessors(&CurMBB); 0
407 ----
408 // Add an edge from CurMBB to NewMBB for the fall-through. ----
409 CurMBB.addSuccessor(NewMBB); 0
410 ----
411 // Splice the code over. ----
412 NewMBB->splice(NewMBB->end(), &CurMBB, BBI1, CurMBB.end()); 0
413 ----
414 // NewMBB belongs to the same loop as CurMBB. ----
415 if (MLI) 0
416 if (MachineLoop *ML = MLI->getLoopFor(&CurMBB)) 0
417 ML->addBasicBlockToLoop(NewMBB, MLI->getBase()); 0
418 ----
419 // NewMBB inherits CurMBB's block frequency. ----
420 MBBFreqInfo.setBlockFreq(NewMBB, MBBFreqInfo.getBlockFreq(&CurMBB)); 0
421 ----
422 if (UpdateLiveIns) 0
423 computeAndAddLiveIns(LiveRegs, *NewMBB); 0
424 ----
425 // Add the new block to the EH scope. ----
426 const auto &EHScopeI = EHScopeMembership.find(&CurMBB); 0
427 if (EHScopeI != EHScopeMembership.end()) { 0
428 auto n = EHScopeI->second; 0
429 EHScopeMembership[NewMBB] = n; 0
430 } ----
431 ----
432 return NewMBB; 0
433 } ----

435 /// EstimateRuntime - Make a rough estimate for how long it will take to run ----
436 /// the specified code. ----
437 static unsigned EstimateRuntime(MachineBasicBlock::iterator I, 0
438 MachineBasicBlock::iterator E) { ----
439 unsigned Time = 0; 0
440 for (; I != E; ++I) { 0
441 if (!countsAsInstruction(*I)) 0
442 continue; 0
443 if (I->isCall()) 0
444 Time += 10; 0
445 else if (I->mayLoadOrStore()) 0
446 Time += 2; 0
447 else ----
448 ++Time; 0
449 } ----
450 return Time; 0
451 } ----
452 ----
453 // CurMBB needs to add an unconditional branch to SuccMBB (we removed these ----
454 // branches temporarily for tail merging). In the case where CurMBB ends ----
455 // with a conditional branch to the next block, optimize by reversing the ----
456 // test and conditionally branching to SuccMBB instead. ----
457 static void FixTail(MachineBasicBlock *CurMBB, MachineBasicBlock *SuccBB, 0
458 const TargetInstrInfo *TII) { ----
459 MachineFunction *MF = CurMBB->getParent(); 0
460 MachineFunction::iterator I = std::next(MachineFunction::iterator(CurMBB)); 0
461 MachineBasicBlock *TBB = nullptr, *FBB = nullptr; 0
462 SmallVector Cond; 0
463 DebugLoc dl = CurMBB->findBranchDebugLoc(); 0
464 if (I != MF->end() && !TII->analyzeBranch(*CurMBB, TBB, FBB, Cond, true)) { 0
465 MachineBasicBlock *NextBB = &*I; 0
466 if (TBB == NextBB && !Cond.empty() && !FBB) { 0
467 if (!TII->reverseBranchCondition(Cond)) { 0
468 TII->removeBranch(*CurMBB); 0
469 TII->insertBranch(*CurMBB, SuccBB, nullptr, Cond, dl); 0
470 return; 0
471 } ----
472 } ----
473 } ----
474 TII->insertBranch(*CurMBB, SuccBB, nullptr, 0
475 SmallVector(), dl); 0
476 } 0

479 BranchFolder::MergePotentialsElt::operator<(const MergePotentialsElt &o) const { 0
480 if (getHash() < o.getHash()) 0
481 return true; 0
482 if (getHash() > o.getHash()) 0
483 return false; 0
484 if (getBlock()->getNumber() < o.getBlock()->getNumber()) 0
485 return true; 0
486 if (getBlock()->getNumber() > o.getBlock()->getNumber()) 0

488 // _GLIBCXX_DEBUG checks strict weak ordering, which involves comparing ----
489 // an object with itself. ----
490 #ifndef _GLIBCXX_DEBUG ----
491 llvm_unreachable("Predecessor appears twice"); 0
492 #else ----
493 return false; ----
494 #endif ----
495 } ----

497 /// CountTerminators - Count the number of terminators in the given ----
498 /// block and set I to the position of the first non-terminator, if there ----
499 /// is one, or MBB->end() otherwise. ----
500 static unsigned CountTerminators(MachineBasicBlock *MBB, 0
501 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &I) { ----
502 I = MBB->end(); 0
503 unsigned NumTerms = 0; 0
504 while (true) { ----
505 if (I == MBB->begin()) { 0
506 I = MBB->end(); 0
507 break; 0
508 } ----
509 --I; 0
510 if (!I->isTerminator()) break; 0
511 ++NumTerms; 0
512 } ----
513 return NumTerms; 0
514 } ----

516 /// A no successor, non-return block probably ends in unreachable and is cold. ----
517 /// Also consider a block that ends in an indirect branch to be a return block, ----
518 /// since many targets use plain indirect branches to return. ----
519 static bool blockEndsInUnreachable(const MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
520 if (!MBB->succ_empty()) 0
521 return false; 0
522 if (MBB->empty()) 0
523 return true; 0
524 return !(MBB->back().isReturn() || MBB->back().isIndirectBranch()); 0
525 } ----
526 ----
527 /// ProfitableToMerge - Check if two machine basic blocks have a common tail ----
528 /// and decide if it would be profitable to merge those tails. Return the ----
529 /// length of the common tail and iterators to the first common instruction ----
530 /// in each block. ----
531 /// MBB1, MBB2 The blocks to check ----
532 /// MinCommonTailLength Minimum size of tail block to be merged. ----
533 /// CommonTailLen Out parameter to record the size of the shared tail between ----
534 /// MBB1 and MBB2 ----
535 /// I1, I2 Iterator references that will be changed to point to the first ----
536 /// instruction in the common tail shared by MBB1,MBB2 ----
537 /// SuccBB A common successor of MBB1, MBB2 which are in a canonical form ----
538 /// relative to SuccBB ----
539 /// PredBB The layout predecessor of SuccBB, if any. ----
540 /// EHScopeMembership map from block to EH scope #. ----
541 /// AfterPlacement True if we are merging blocks after layout. Stricter ----
542 /// thresholds apply to prevent undoing tail-duplication. ----
543 static bool ----
544 ProfitableToMerge(MachineBasicBlock *MBB1, MachineBasicBlock *MBB2, 0
545 unsigned MinCommonTailLength, unsigned &CommonTailLen, ----
546 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &I1, ----
547 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &I2, MachineBasicBlock *SuccBB, ----
548 MachineBasicBlock *PredBB, ----
549 DenseMap &EHScopeMembership, ----
550 bool AfterPlacement, ----
551 MBFIWrapper &MBBFreqInfo, ----
552 ProfileSummaryInfo *PSI) { ----
553 // It is never profitable to tail-merge blocks from two different EH scopes. ----
554 if (!EHScopeMembership.empty()) { 0
555 auto EHScope1 = EHScopeMembership.find(MBB1); 0
556 assert(EHScope1 != EHScopeMembership.end()); 0
557 auto EHScope2 = EHScopeMembership.find(MBB2); 0
558 assert(EHScope2 != EHScopeMembership.end()); 0
559 if (EHScope1->second != EHScope2->second) 0
560 return false; 0
561 } ----
562 ----
563 CommonTailLen = ComputeCommonTailLength(MBB1, MBB2, I1, I2); 0
564 if (CommonTailLen == 0) 0
565 return false; 0
566 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Common tail length of " << printMBBReference(*MBB1) 0
567 << " and " << printMBBReference(*MBB2) << " is " ----
568 << CommonTailLen << '\n'); ----
569 ----
570 // Move the iterators to the beginning of the MBB if we only got debug ----
571 // instructions before the tail. This is to avoid splitting a block when we ----
572 // only got debug instructions before the tail (to be invariant on -g). ----
573 if (skipDebugInstructionsForward(MBB1->begin(), MBB1->end(), false) == I1) 0
574 I1 = MBB1->begin(); 0
575 if (skipDebugInstructionsForward(MBB2->begin(), MBB2->end(), false) == I2) 0
576 I2 = MBB2->begin(); 0
577 ----
578 bool FullBlockTail1 = I1 == MBB1->begin(); 0
579 bool FullBlockTail2 = I2 == MBB2->begin(); 0
580 ----
581 // It's almost always profitable to merge any number of non-terminator ----
582 // instructions with the block that falls through into the common successor. ----
583 // This is true only for a single successor. For multiple successors, we are ----
584 // trading a conditional branch for an unconditional one. ----
585 // TODO: Re-visit successor size for non-layout tail merging. ----
586 if ((MBB1 == PredBB || MBB2 == PredBB) && 0
587 (!AfterPlacement || MBB1->succ_size() == 1)) { 0
588 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I; 0
589 unsigned NumTerms = CountTerminators(MBB1 == PredBB ? MBB2 : MBB1, I); 0
590 if (CommonTailLen > NumTerms) 0
591 return true; 0
592 } ----
593 ----
594 // If these are identical non-return blocks with no successors, merge them. ----
595 // Such blocks are typically cold calls to noreturn functions like abort, and ----
596 // are unlikely to become a fallthrough target after machine block placement. ----
597 // Tail merging these blocks is unlikely to create additional unconditional ----
598 // branches, and will reduce the size of this cold code. ----
599 if (FullBlockTail1 && FullBlockTail2 && 0
600 blockEndsInUnreachable(MBB1) && blockEndsInUnreachable(MBB2)) 0
601 return true; 0
602 ----
603 // If one of the blocks can be completely merged and happens to be in ----
604 // a position where the other could fall through into it, merge any number ----
605 // of instructions, because it can be done without a branch. ----
606 // TODO: If the blocks are not adjacent, move one of them so that they are? ----
607 if (MBB1->isLayoutSuccessor(MBB2) && FullBlockTail2) 0
608 return true; 0
609 if (MBB2->isLayoutSuccessor(MBB1) && FullBlockTail1) 0
610 return true; 0
611 ----
612 // If both blocks are identical and end in a branch, merge them unless they ----
613 // both have a fallthrough predecessor and successor. ----
614 // We can only do this after block placement because it depends on whether ----
615 // there are fallthroughs, and we don't know until after layout. ----
616 if (AfterPlacement && FullBlockTail1 && FullBlockTail2) { 0
617 auto BothFallThrough = [](MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
618 if (!MBB->succ_empty() && !MBB->canFallThrough()) 0
619 return false; 0
620 MachineFunction::iterator I(MBB); 0
621 MachineFunction *MF = MBB->getParent(); 0
622 return (MBB != &*MF->begin()) && std::prev(I)->canFallThrough(); 0
623 }; ----
624 if (!BothFallThrough(MBB1) || !BothFallThrough(MBB2)) 0
625 return true; 0
626 } ----
627 ----
628 // If both blocks have an unconditional branch temporarily stripped out, ----
629 // count that as an additional common instruction for the following ----
630 // heuristics. This heuristic is only accurate for single-succ blocks, so to ----
631 // make sure that during layout merging and duplicating don't crash, we check ----
632 // for that when merging during layout. ----
633 unsigned EffectiveTailLen = CommonTailLen; 0
634 if (SuccBB && MBB1 != PredBB && MBB2 != PredBB && 0
635 (MBB1->succ_size() == 1 || !AfterPlacement) && 0
636 !MBB1->back().isBarrier() && 0
637 !MBB2->back().isBarrier()) 0
638 ++EffectiveTailLen; 0
639 ----
640 // Check if the common tail is long enough to be worthwhile. ----
641 if (EffectiveTailLen >= MinCommonTailLength) 0
642 return true; 0
643 ----
644 // If we are optimizing for code size, 2 instructions in common is enough if ----
645 // we don't have to split a block. At worst we will be introducing 1 new ----
646 // branch instruction, which is likely to be smaller than the 2 ----
647 // instructions that would be deleted in the merge. ----
648 MachineFunction *MF = MBB1->getParent(); 0
649 bool OptForSize = ----
650 MF->getFunction().hasOptSize() || 0
651 (llvm::shouldOptimizeForSize(MBB1, PSI, &MBBFreqInfo) && 0
652 llvm::shouldOptimizeForSize(MBB2, PSI, &MBBFreqInfo)); 0
653 return EffectiveTailLen >= 2 && OptForSize && 0
654 (FullBlockTail1 || FullBlockTail2); 0
655 } ----
656 ----
657 unsigned BranchFolder::ComputeSameTails(unsigned CurHash, 0
658 unsigned MinCommonTailLength, ----
659 MachineBasicBlock *SuccBB, ----
660 MachineBasicBlock *PredBB) { ----
661 unsigned maxCommonTailLength = 0U; 0
662 SameTails.clear(); 0
663 MachineBasicBlock::iterator TrialBBI1, TrialBBI2; 0
664 MPIterator HighestMPIter = std::prev(MergePotentials.end()); 0
665 for (MPIterator CurMPIter = std::prev(MergePotentials.end()), 0
666 B = MergePotentials.begin(); 0
667 CurMPIter != B && CurMPIter->getHash() == CurHash; --CurMPIter) { 0
668 for (MPIterator I = std::prev(CurMPIter); I->getHash() == CurHash; --I) { 0
669 unsigned CommonTailLen; ----
670 if (ProfitableToMerge(CurMPIter->getBlock(), I->getBlock(), 0
671 MinCommonTailLength, ----
672 CommonTailLen, TrialBBI1, TrialBBI2, ----
673 SuccBB, PredBB, ----
674 EHScopeMembership, 0
675 AfterBlockPlacement, MBBFreqInfo, PSI)) { 0
676 if (CommonTailLen > maxCommonTailLength) { 0
677 SameTails.clear(); 0
678 maxCommonTailLength = CommonTailLen; 0
679 HighestMPIter = CurMPIter; 0
680 SameTails.push_back(SameTailElt(CurMPIter, TrialBBI1)); 0
681 } ----
682 if (HighestMPIter == CurMPIter && 0
683 CommonTailLen == maxCommonTailLength) 0
684 SameTails.push_back(SameTailElt(I, TrialBBI2)); 0
685 } ----
686 if (I == B) 0
687 break; 0
688 } ----
689 } ----
690 return maxCommonTailLength; 0
691 } ----
692 ----
693 void BranchFolder::RemoveBlocksWithHash(unsigned CurHash, 0
694 MachineBasicBlock *SuccBB, ----
695 MachineBasicBlock *PredBB) { ----
696 MPIterator CurMPIter, B; 0
697 for (CurMPIter = std::prev(MergePotentials.end()), 0
698 B = MergePotentials.begin(); 0
699 CurMPIter->getHash() == CurHash; --CurMPIter) { 0
700 // Put the unconditional branch back, if we need one. ----
701 MachineBasicBlock *CurMBB = CurMPIter->getBlock(); 0
702 if (SuccBB && CurMBB != PredBB) 0
703 FixTail(CurMBB, SuccBB, TII); 0
704 if (CurMPIter == B) 0
705 break; 0
706 } ----
707 if (CurMPIter->getHash() != CurHash) 0
708 CurMPIter++; 0
709 MergePotentials.erase(CurMPIter, MergePotentials.end()); 0
710 } 0
711 ----
712 bool BranchFolder::CreateCommonTailOnlyBlock(MachineBasicBlock *&PredBB, 0
713 MachineBasicBlock *SuccBB, ----
714 unsigned maxCommonTailLength, ----
715 unsigned &commonTailIndex) { ----
716 commonTailIndex = 0; 0
717 unsigned TimeEstimate = ~0U; 0
718 for (unsigned i = 0, e = SameTails.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
719 // Use PredBB if possible; that doesn't require a new branch. ----
720 if (SameTails[i].getBlock() == PredBB) { 0
721 commonTailIndex = i; 0
722 break; 0
723 } ----
724 // Otherwise, make a (fairly bogus) choice based on estimate of ----
725 // how long it will take the various blocks to execute. ----
726 unsigned t = EstimateRuntime(SameTails[i].getBlock()->begin(), 0
727 SameTails[i].getTailStartPos()); 0
728 if (t <= TimeEstimate) { 0
729 TimeEstimate = t; 0
730 commonTailIndex = i; 0
731 } ----
732 } ----
733 ----
734 MachineBasicBlock::iterator BBI = ----
735 SameTails[commonTailIndex].getTailStartPos(); 0
736 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = SameTails[commonTailIndex].getBlock(); 0
737 ----
738 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nSplitting " << printMBBReference(*MBB) << ", size " 0
739 << maxCommonTailLength); ----
740 ----
741 // If the split block unconditionally falls-thru to SuccBB, it will be ----
742 // merged. In control flow terms it should then take SuccBB's name. e.g. If ----
743 // SuccBB is an inner loop, the common tail is still part of the inner loop. ----
744 const BasicBlock *BB = (SuccBB && MBB->succ_size() == 1) ? 0
745 SuccBB->getBasicBlock() : MBB->getBasicBlock(); 0
746 MachineBasicBlock *newMBB = SplitMBBAt(*MBB, BBI, BB); 0
747 if (!newMBB) { 0
748 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "... failed!"); 0
749 return false; 0
750 } ----
751 ----
752 SameTails[commonTailIndex].setBlock(newMBB); 0
753 SameTails[commonTailIndex].setTailStartPos(newMBB->begin()); 0
754 ----
755 // If we split PredBB, newMBB is the new predecessor. ----
756 if (PredBB == MBB) 0
757 PredBB = newMBB; 0
758 ----
759 return true; 0
760 } ----
761 ----
762 static void ----
763 mergeOperations(MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBIStartPos, 0
764 MachineBasicBlock &MBBCommon) { ----
765 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MBBIStartPos->getParent(); 0
766 // Note CommonTailLen does not necessarily matches the size of ----
767 // the common BB nor all its instructions because of debug ----
768 // instructions differences. ----
769 unsigned CommonTailLen = 0; 0
770 for (auto E = MBB->end(); MBBIStartPos != E; ++MBBIStartPos) 0
771 ++CommonTailLen; 0
772 ----
773 MachineBasicBlock::reverse_iterator MBBI = MBB->rbegin(); 0
774 MachineBasicBlock::reverse_iterator MBBIE = MBB->rend(); 0
775 MachineBasicBlock::reverse_iterator MBBICommon = MBBCommon.rbegin(); 0
776 MachineBasicBlock::reverse_iterator MBBIECommon = MBBCommon.rend(); 0
777 ----
778 while (CommonTailLen--) { 0
779 assert(MBBI != MBBIE && "Reached BB end within common tail length!"); 0
780 (void)MBBIE; ----
781 ----
782 if (!countsAsInstruction(*MBBI)) { 0
783 ++MBBI; 0
784 continue; 0
785 } ----
786 ----
787 while ((MBBICommon != MBBIECommon) && !countsAsInstruction(*MBBICommon)) 0
788 ++MBBICommon; 0
789 ----
790 assert(MBBICommon != MBBIECommon && 0
791 "Reached BB end within common tail length!"); ----
792 assert(MBBICommon->isIdenticalTo(*MBBI) && "Expected matching MIIs!"); 0
793 ----
794 // Merge MMOs from memory operations in the common block. ----
795 if (MBBICommon->mayLoadOrStore()) 0
796 MBBICommon->cloneMergedMemRefs(*MBB->getParent(), {&*MBBICommon, &*MBBI}); 0
797 // Drop undef flags if they aren't present in all merged instructions. ----
798 for (unsigned I = 0, E = MBBICommon->getNumOperands(); I != E; ++I) { 0
799 MachineOperand &MO = MBBICommon->getOperand(I); 0
800 if (MO.isReg() && MO.isUndef()) { 0
801 const MachineOperand &OtherMO = MBBI->getOperand(I); 0
802 if (!OtherMO.isUndef()) 0
803 MO.setIsUndef(false); 0
804 } ----
805 } ----
806 ----
807 ++MBBI; 0
808 ++MBBICommon; 0
809 } ----
810 } 0
811 ----
812 void BranchFolder::mergeCommonTails(unsigned commonTailIndex) { 0
813 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = SameTails[commonTailIndex].getBlock(); 0
814 ----
815 std::vector NextCommonInsts(SameTails.size()); 0
816 for (unsigned int i = 0 ; i != SameTails.size() ; ++i) { 0
817 if (i != commonTailIndex) { 0
818 NextCommonInsts[i] = SameTails[i].getTailStartPos(); 0
819 mergeOperations(SameTails[i].getTailStartPos(), *MBB); 0
820 } else { ----
821 assert(SameTails[i].getTailStartPos() == MBB->begin() && 0
822 "MBB is not a common tail only block"); ----
823 } ----
824 } ----
825 ----
826 for (auto &MI : *MBB) { 0
827 if (!countsAsInstruction(MI)) 0
828 continue; 0
829 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
830 for (unsigned int i = 0 ; i < NextCommonInsts.size() ; i++) { 0
831 if (i == commonTailIndex) 0
832 continue; 0
833 ----
834 auto &Pos = NextCommonInsts[i]; 0
835 assert(Pos != SameTails[i].getBlock()->end() && 0
836 "Reached BB end within common tail"); ----
837 while (!countsAsInstruction(*Pos)) { 0
838 ++Pos; 0
839 assert(Pos != SameTails[i].getBlock()->end() && 0
840 "Reached BB end within common tail"); ----
841 } ----
842 assert(MI.isIdenticalTo(*Pos) && "Expected matching MIIs!"); 0
843 DL = DILocation::getMergedLocation(DL, Pos->getDebugLoc()); 0
844 NextCommonInsts[i] = ++Pos; 0
845 } ----
846 MI.setDebugLoc(DL); 0
847 } 0
848 ----
849 if (UpdateLiveIns) { 0
850 LivePhysRegs NewLiveIns(*TRI); 0
851 computeLiveIns(NewLiveIns, *MBB); 0
852 LiveRegs.init(*TRI); 0
853 ----
854 // The flag merging may lead to some register uses no longer using the ----
855 // flag, add IMPLICIT_DEFs in the predecessors as necessary. ----
856 for (MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB->predecessors()) { 0
857 LiveRegs.clear(); 0
858 LiveRegs.addLiveOuts(*Pred); 0
859 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertBefore = Pred->getFirstTerminator(); 0
860 for (Register Reg : NewLiveIns) { 0
861 if (!LiveRegs.available(*MRI, Reg)) 0
862 continue; 0
863 ----
864 // Skip the register if we are about to add one of its super registers. ----
865 // TODO: Common this up with the same logic in addLineIns(). ----
866 if (any_of(TRI->superregs(Reg), [&](MCPhysReg SReg) { 0
867 return NewLiveIns.contains(SReg) && !MRI->isReserved(SReg); 0
868 })) ----
869 continue; 0
870 ----
871 DebugLoc DL; 0
872 BuildMI(*Pred, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF), 0
873 Reg); ----
874 } 0
875 } ----
876 ----
877 MBB->clearLiveIns(); 0
878 addLiveIns(*MBB, NewLiveIns); 0
879 } 0
880 } 0
881 ----
882 // See if any of the blocks in MergePotentials (which all have SuccBB as a ----
883 // successor, or all have no successor if it is null) can be tail-merged. ----
884 // If there is a successor, any blocks in MergePotentials that are not ----
885 // tail-merged and are not immediately before Succ must have an unconditional ----
886 // branch to Succ added (but the predecessor/successor lists need no ----
887 // adjustment). The lone predecessor of Succ that falls through into Succ, ----
888 // if any, is given in PredBB. ----
889 // MinCommonTailLength - Except for the special cases below, tail-merge if ----
890 // there are at least this many instructions in common. ----
891 bool BranchFolder::TryTailMergeBlocks(MachineBasicBlock *SuccBB, 0
892 MachineBasicBlock *PredBB, ----
893 unsigned MinCommonTailLength) { ----
894 bool MadeChange = false; 0
895 ----
896 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
897 dbgs() << "\nTryTailMergeBlocks: "; ----
898 for (unsigned i = 0, e = MergePotentials.size(); i != e; ++i) dbgs() ----
899 << printMBBReference(*MergePotentials[i].getBlock()) ----
900 << (i == e - 1 ? "" : ", "); ----
901 dbgs() << "\n"; if (SuccBB) { ----
902 dbgs() << " with successor " << printMBBReference(*SuccBB) << '\n'; ----
903 if (PredBB) ----
904 dbgs() << " which has fall-through from " ----
905 << printMBBReference(*PredBB) << "\n"; ----
906 } dbgs() << "Looking for common tails of at least " ----
907 << MinCommonTailLength << " instruction" ----
908 << (MinCommonTailLength == 1 ? "" : "s") << '\n';); ----
909 ----
910 // Sort by hash value so that blocks with identical end sequences sort ----
911 // together. ----
912 array_pod_sort(MergePotentials.begin(), MergePotentials.end()); 0
913 ----
914 // Walk through equivalence sets looking for actual exact matches. ----
915 while (MergePotentials.size() > 1) { 0
916 unsigned CurHash = MergePotentials.back().getHash(); 0
917 ----
918 // Build SameTails, identifying the set of blocks with this hash code ----
919 // and with the maximum number of instructions in common. ----
920 unsigned maxCommonTailLength = ComputeSameTails(CurHash, 0
921 MinCommonTailLength, ----
922 SuccBB, PredBB); ----
923 ----
924 // If we didn't find any pair that has at least MinCommonTailLength ----
925 // instructions in common, remove all blocks with this hash code and retry. ----
926 if (SameTails.empty()) { 0
927 RemoveBlocksWithHash(CurHash, SuccBB, PredBB); 0
928 continue; 0
929 } ----
930 ----
931 // If one of the blocks is the entire common tail (and is not the entry ----
932 // block/an EH pad, which we can't jump to), we can treat all blocks with ----
933 // this same tail at once. Use PredBB if that is one of the possibilities, ----
934 // as that will not introduce any extra branches. ----
935 MachineBasicBlock *EntryBB = ----
936 &MergePotentials.front().getBlock()->getParent()->front(); 0
937 unsigned commonTailIndex = SameTails.size(); 0
938 // If there are two blocks, check to see if one can be made to fall through ----
939 // into the other. ----
940 if (SameTails.size() == 2 && 0
941 SameTails[0].getBlock()->isLayoutSuccessor(SameTails[1].getBlock()) && 0
942 SameTails[1].tailIsWholeBlock() && !SameTails[1].getBlock()->isEHPad()) 0
943 commonTailIndex = 1; 0
944 else if (SameTails.size() == 2 && 0
945 SameTails[1].getBlock()->isLayoutSuccessor( 0
946 SameTails[0].getBlock()) && 0
947 SameTails[0].tailIsWholeBlock() && 0
948 !SameTails[0].getBlock()->isEHPad()) 0
949 commonTailIndex = 0; 0
950 else { ----
951 // Otherwise just pick one, favoring the fall-through predecessor if ----
952 // there is one. ----
953 for (unsigned i = 0, e = SameTails.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
954 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = SameTails[i].getBlock(); 0
955 if ((MBB == EntryBB || MBB->isEHPad()) && 0
956 SameTails[i].tailIsWholeBlock()) 0
957 continue; 0
958 if (MBB == PredBB) { 0
959 commonTailIndex = i; 0
960 break; 0
961 } ----
962 if (SameTails[i].tailIsWholeBlock()) 0
963 commonTailIndex = i; 0
964 } ----
965 } ----
966 ----
967 if (commonTailIndex == SameTails.size() || 0
968 (SameTails[commonTailIndex].getBlock() == PredBB && 0
969 !SameTails[commonTailIndex].tailIsWholeBlock())) { 0
970 // None of the blocks consist entirely of the common tail. ----
971 // Split a block so that one does. ----
972 if (!CreateCommonTailOnlyBlock(PredBB, SuccBB, 0
973 maxCommonTailLength, commonTailIndex)) { ----
974 RemoveBlocksWithHash(CurHash, SuccBB, PredBB); 0
975 continue; 0
976 } ----
977 } ----
978 ----
979 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = SameTails[commonTailIndex].getBlock(); 0
980 ----
981 // Recompute common tail MBB's edge weights and block frequency. ----
982 setCommonTailEdgeWeights(*MBB); 0
983 ----
984 // Merge debug locations, MMOs and undef flags across identical instructions ----
985 // for common tail. ----
986 mergeCommonTails(commonTailIndex); 0
987 ----
988 // MBB is common tail. Adjust all other BB's to jump to this one. ----
989 // Traversal must be forwards so erases work. ----
990 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nUsing common tail in " << printMBBReference(*MBB) 0
991 << " for "); ----
992 for (unsigned int i=0, e = SameTails.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
993 if (commonTailIndex == i) 0
994 continue; 0
995 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << printMBBReference(*SameTails[i].getBlock()) 0
996 << (i == e - 1 ? "" : ", ")); ----
997 // Hack the end off BB i, making it jump to BB commonTailIndex instead. ----
998 replaceTailWithBranchTo(SameTails[i].getTailStartPos(), *MBB); 0
999 // BB i is no longer a predecessor of SuccBB; remove it from the worklist. ----
1000 MergePotentials.erase(SameTails[i].getMPIter()); 0
1001 } ----
1002 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n"); 0
1003 // We leave commonTailIndex in the worklist in case there are other blocks ----
1004 // that match it with a smaller number of instructions. ----
1005 MadeChange = true; 0
1006 } ----
1007 return MadeChange; 0
1008 } ----
1009 ----
1010 bool BranchFolder::TailMergeBlocks(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
1011 bool MadeChange = false; 0
1012 if (!EnableTailMerge) 0
1013 return MadeChange; 0
1014 ----
1015 // First find blocks with no successors. ----
1016 // Block placement may create new tail merging opportunities for these blocks. ----
1017 MergePotentials.clear(); 0
1018 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) { 0
1019 if (MergePotentials.size() == TailMergeThreshold) 0
1020 break; 0
1021 if (!TriedMerging.count(&MBB) && MBB.succ_empty()) 0
1022 MergePotentials.push_back(MergePotentialsElt(HashEndOfMBB(MBB), &MBB)); 0
1023 } ----
1024 ----
1025 // If this is a large problem, avoid visiting the same basic blocks ----
1026 // multiple times. ----
1027 if (MergePotentials.size() == TailMergeThreshold) 0
1028 for (const MergePotentialsElt &Elt : MergePotentials) 0
1029 TriedMerging.insert(Elt.getBlock()); 0
1030 ----
1031 // See if we can do any tail merging on those. ----
1032 if (MergePotentials.size() >= 2) 0
1033 MadeChange |= TryTailMergeBlocks(nullptr, nullptr, MinCommonTailLength); 0
1034 ----
1035 // Look at blocks (IBB) with multiple predecessors (PBB). ----
1036 // We change each predecessor to a canonical form, by ----
1037 // (1) temporarily removing any unconditional branch from the predecessor ----
1038 // to IBB, and ----
1039 // (2) alter conditional branches so they branch to the other block ----
1040 // not IBB; this may require adding back an unconditional branch to IBB ----
1041 // later, where there wasn't one coming in. E.g. ----
1042 // Bcc IBB ----
1043 // fallthrough to QBB ----
1044 // here becomes ----
1045 // Bncc QBB ----
1046 // with a conceptual B to IBB after that, which never actually exists. ----
1047 // With those changes, we see whether the predecessors' tails match, ----
1048 // and merge them if so. We change things out of canonical form and ----
1049 // back to the way they were later in the process. (OptimizeBranches ----
1050 // would undo some of this, but we can't use it, because we'd get into ----
1051 // a compile-time infinite loop repeatedly doing and undoing the same ----
1052 // transformations.) ----
1053 ----
1054 for (MachineFunction::iterator I = std::next(MF.begin()), E = MF.end(); 0
1055 I != E; ++I) { 0
1056 if (I->pred_size() < 2) continue; 0
1057 SmallPtrSet UniquePreds; 0
1058 MachineBasicBlock *IBB = &*I; 0
1059 MachineBasicBlock *PredBB = &*std::prev(I); 0
1060 MergePotentials.clear(); 0
1061 MachineLoop *ML; ----
1062 ----
1063 // Bail if merging after placement and IBB is the loop header because ----
1064 // -- If merging predecessors that belong to the same loop as IBB, the ----
1065 // common tail of merged predecessors may become the loop top if block ----
1066 // placement is called again and the predecessors may branch to this common ----
1067 // tail and require more branches. This can be relaxed if ----
1068 // MachineBlockPlacement::findBestLoopTop is more flexible. ----
1069 // --If merging predecessors that do not belong to the same loop as IBB, the ----
1070 // loop info of IBB's loop and the other loops may be affected. Calling the ----
1071 // block placement again may make big change to the layout and eliminate the ----
1072 // reason to do tail merging here. ----
1073 if (AfterBlockPlacement && MLI) { 0
1074 ML = MLI->getLoopFor(IBB); 0
1075 if (ML && IBB == ML->getHeader()) 0
1076 continue; 0
1077 } ----
1078 ----
1079 for (MachineBasicBlock *PBB : I->predecessors()) { 0
1080 if (MergePotentials.size() == TailMergeThreshold) 0
1081 break; 0
1082 ----
1083 if (TriedMerging.count(PBB)) 0
1084 continue; 0
1085 ----
1086 // Skip blocks that loop to themselves, can't tail merge these. ----
1087 if (PBB == IBB) 0
1088 continue; 0
1089 ----
1090 // Visit each predecessor only once. ----
1091 if (!UniquePreds.insert(PBB).second) 0
1092 continue; 0
1093 ----
1094 // Skip blocks which may jump to a landing pad or jump from an asm blob. ----
1095 // Can't tail merge these. ----
1096 if (PBB->hasEHPadSuccessor() || PBB->mayHaveInlineAsmBr()) 0
1097 continue; 0
1098 ----
1099 // After block placement, only consider predecessors that belong to the ----
1100 // same loop as IBB. The reason is the same as above when skipping loop ----
1101 // header. ----
1102 if (AfterBlockPlacement && MLI) 0
1103 if (ML != MLI->getLoopFor(PBB)) 0
1104 continue; 0
1105 ----
1106 MachineBasicBlock *TBB = nullptr, *FBB = nullptr; 0
1107 SmallVector Cond; 0
1108 if (!TII->analyzeBranch(*PBB, TBB, FBB, Cond, true)) { 0
1109 // Failing case: IBB is the target of a cbr, and we cannot reverse the ----
1110 // branch. ----
1111 SmallVector NewCond(Cond); 0
1112 if (!Cond.empty() && TBB == IBB) { 0
1113 if (TII->reverseBranchCondition(NewCond)) 0
1114 continue; 0
1115 // This is the QBB case described above ----
1116 if (!FBB) { 0
1117 auto Next = ++PBB->getIterator(); 0
1118 if (Next != MF.end()) 0
1119 FBB = &*Next; 0
1120 } ----
1121 } ----
1122 ----
1123 // Remove the unconditional branch at the end, if any. ----
1124 if (TBB && (Cond.empty() || FBB)) { 0
1125 DebugLoc dl = PBB->findBranchDebugLoc(); 0
1126 TII->removeBranch(*PBB); 0
1127 if (!Cond.empty()) 0
1128 // reinsert conditional branch only, for now ----
1129 TII->insertBranch(*PBB, (TBB == IBB) ? FBB : TBB, nullptr, 0
1130 NewCond, dl); ----
1131 } 0
1132 ----
1133 MergePotentials.push_back(MergePotentialsElt(HashEndOfMBB(*PBB), PBB)); 0
1134 } 0
1135 } 0
1136 ----
1137 // If this is a large problem, avoid visiting the same basic blocks multiple ----
1138 // times. ----
1139 if (MergePotentials.size() == TailMergeThreshold) 0
1140 for (MergePotentialsElt &Elt : MergePotentials) 0
1141 TriedMerging.insert(Elt.getBlock()); 0
1142 ----
1143 if (MergePotentials.size() >= 2) 0
1144 MadeChange |= TryTailMergeBlocks(IBB, PredBB, MinCommonTailLength); 0
1145 ----
1146 // Reinsert an unconditional branch if needed. The 1 below can occur as a ----
1147 // result of removing blocks in TryTailMergeBlocks. ----
1148 PredBB = &*std::prev(I); // this may have been changed in TryTailMergeBlocks 0
1149 if (MergePotentials.size() == 1 && 0
1150 MergePotentials.begin()->getBlock() != PredBB) 0
1151 FixTail(MergePotentials.begin()->getBlock(), IBB, TII); 0
1152 } 0
1153 ----
1154 return MadeChange; 0
1155 } ----
1156 ----
1157 void BranchFolder::setCommonTailEdgeWeights(MachineBasicBlock &TailMBB) { 0
1158 SmallVector EdgeFreqLs(TailMBB.succ_size()); 0
1159 BlockFrequency AccumulatedMBBFreq; 0
1160 ----
1161 // Aggregate edge frequency of successor edge j: ----
1162 // edgeFreq(j) = sum (freq(bb) * edgeProb(bb, j)), ----
1163 // where bb is a basic block that is in SameTails. ----
1164 for (const auto &Src : SameTails) { 0
1165 const MachineBasicBlock *SrcMBB = Src.getBlock(); 0
1166 BlockFrequency BlockFreq = MBBFreqInfo.getBlockFreq(SrcMBB); 0
1167 AccumulatedMBBFreq += BlockFreq; 0
1168 ----
1169 // It is not necessary to recompute edge weights if TailBB has less than two ----
1170 // successors. ----
1171 if (TailMBB.succ_size() <= 1) 0
1172 continue; 0
1173 ----
1174 auto EdgeFreq = EdgeFreqLs.begin(); 0
1175 ----
1176 for (auto SuccI = TailMBB.succ_begin(), SuccE = TailMBB.succ_end(); 0
1177 SuccI != SuccE; ++SuccI, ++EdgeFreq) 0
1178 *EdgeFreq += BlockFreq * MBPI.getEdgeProbability(SrcMBB, *SuccI); 0
1179 } ----
1180 ----
1181 MBBFreqInfo.setBlockFreq(&TailMBB, AccumulatedMBBFreq); 0
1182 ----
1183 if (TailMBB.succ_size() <= 1) 0
1184 return; 0
1185 ----
1186 auto SumEdgeFreq = ----
1187 std::accumulate(EdgeFreqLs.begin(), EdgeFreqLs.end(), BlockFrequency(0)) 0
1188 .getFrequency(); 0
1189 auto EdgeFreq = EdgeFreqLs.begin(); 0
1190 ----
1191 if (SumEdgeFreq > 0) { 0
1192 for (auto SuccI = TailMBB.succ_begin(), SuccE = TailMBB.succ_end(); 0
1193 SuccI != SuccE; ++SuccI, ++EdgeFreq) { 0
1194 auto Prob = BranchProbability::getBranchProbability( 0
1195 EdgeFreq->getFrequency(), SumEdgeFreq); ----
1196 TailMBB.setSuccProbability(SuccI, Prob); 0
1197 } ----
1198 } ----
1199 } 0
1200 ----
1201 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1202 // Branch Optimization ----
1203 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1204 ----
1205 bool BranchFolder::OptimizeBranches(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
1206 bool MadeChange = false; 0
1207 ----
1208 // Make sure blocks are numbered in order ----
1209 MF.RenumberBlocks(); 0
1210 // Renumbering blocks alters EH scope membership, recalculate it. ----
1211 EHScopeMembership = getEHScopeMembership(MF); 0
1212 ----
1213 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : 0
1214 llvm::make_early_inc_range(llvm::drop_begin(MF))) { 0
1215 MadeChange |= OptimizeBlock(&MBB); 0
1216 ----
1217 // If it is dead, remove it. ----
1218 if (MBB.pred_empty() && !MBB.isMachineBlockAddressTaken()) { 0
1219 RemoveDeadBlock(&MBB); 0
1220 MadeChange = true; 0
1221 ++NumDeadBlocks; 0
1222 } ----
1223 } ----
1224 ----
1225 return MadeChange; 0
1226 } ----
1227 ----
1228 // Blocks should be considered empty if they contain only debug info; ----
1229 // else the debug info would affect codegen. ----
1230 static bool IsEmptyBlock(MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
1231 return MBB->getFirstNonDebugInstr(true) == MBB->end(); 0
1232 } ----
1233 ----
1234 // Blocks with only debug info and branches should be considered the same ----
1235 // as blocks with only branches. ----
1236 static bool IsBranchOnlyBlock(MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
1237 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = MBB->getFirstNonDebugInstr(); 0
1238 assert(I != MBB->end() && "empty block!"); 0
1239 return I->isBranch(); 0
1240 } ----
1241 ----
1242 /// IsBetterFallthrough - Return true if it would be clearly better to ----
1243 /// fall-through to MBB1 than to fall through into MBB2. This has to return ----
1244 /// a strict ordering, returning true for both (MBB1,MBB2) and (MBB2,MBB1) will ----
1245 /// result in infinite loops. ----
1246 static bool IsBetterFallthrough(MachineBasicBlock *MBB1, 0
1247 MachineBasicBlock *MBB2) { ----
1248 assert(MBB1 && MBB2 && "Unknown MachineBasicBlock"); 0
1249 ----
1250 // Right now, we use a simple heuristic. If MBB2 ends with a call, and ----
1251 // MBB1 doesn't, we prefer to fall through into MBB1. This allows us to ----
1252 // optimize branches that branch to either a return block or an assert block ----
1253 // into a fallthrough to the return. ----
1254 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBB1I = MBB1->getLastNonDebugInstr(); 0
1255 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBB2I = MBB2->getLastNonDebugInstr(); 0
1256 if (MBB1I == MBB1->end() || MBB2I == MBB2->end()) 0
1257 return false; 0
1258 ----
1259 // If there is a clear successor ordering we make sure that one block ----
1260 // will fall through to the next ----
1261 if (MBB1->isSuccessor(MBB2)) return true; 0
1262 if (MBB2->isSuccessor(MBB1)) return false; 0
1263 ----
1264 return MBB2I->isCall() && !MBB1I->isCall(); 0
1265 } ----
1266 ----
1267 /// getBranchDebugLoc - Find and return, if any, the DebugLoc of the branch ----
1268 /// instructions on the block. ----
1269 static DebugLoc getBranchDebugLoc(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
1270 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = MBB.getLastNonDebugInstr(); 0
1271 if (I != MBB.end() && I->isBranch()) 0
1272 return I->getDebugLoc(); 0
1273 return DebugLoc(); 0
1274 } ----
1275 ----
1276 static void copyDebugInfoToPredecessor(const TargetInstrInfo *TII, 0
1277 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, ----
1278 MachineBasicBlock &PredMBB) { ----
1279 auto InsertBefore = PredMBB.getFirstTerminator(); 0
1280 for (MachineInstr &MI : MBB.instrs()) 0
1281 if (MI.isDebugInstr()) { 0
1282 TII->duplicate(PredMBB, InsertBefore, MI); 0
1283 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Copied debug entity from empty block to pred: " 0
1284 << MI); ----
1285 } ----
1286 } 0
1287 ----
1288 static void copyDebugInfoToSuccessor(const TargetInstrInfo *TII, 0
1289 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, ----
1290 MachineBasicBlock &SuccMBB) { ----
1291 auto InsertBefore = SuccMBB.SkipPHIsAndLabels(SuccMBB.begin()); 0
1292 for (MachineInstr &MI : MBB.instrs()) 0
1293 if (MI.isDebugInstr()) { 0
1294 TII->duplicate(SuccMBB, InsertBefore, MI); 0
1295 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Copied debug entity from empty block to succ: " 0
1296 << MI); ----
1297 } ----
1298 } 0
1299 ----
1300 // Try to salvage DBG_VALUE instructions from an otherwise empty block. If such ----
1301 // a basic block is removed we would lose the debug information unless we have ----
1302 // copied the information to a predecessor/successor. ----
1303 // ----
1304 // TODO: This function only handles some simple cases. An alternative would be ----
1305 // to run a heavier analysis, such as the LiveDebugValues pass, before we do ----
1306 // branch folding. ----
1307 static void salvageDebugInfoFromEmptyBlock(const TargetInstrInfo *TII, 0
1308 MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { ----
1309 assert(IsEmptyBlock(&MBB) && "Expected an empty block (except debug info)."); 0
1310 // If this MBB is the only predecessor of a successor it is legal to copy ----
1311 // DBG_VALUE instructions to the beginning of the successor. ----
1312 for (MachineBasicBlock *SuccBB : MBB.successors()) 0
1313 if (SuccBB->pred_size() == 1) 0
1314 copyDebugInfoToSuccessor(TII, MBB, *SuccBB); 0
1315 // If this MBB is the only successor of a predecessor it is legal to copy the ----
1316 // DBG_VALUE instructions to the end of the predecessor (just before the ----
1317 // terminators, assuming that the terminator isn't affecting the DBG_VALUE). ----
1318 for (MachineBasicBlock *PredBB : MBB.predecessors()) 0
1319 if (PredBB->succ_size() == 1) 0
1320 copyDebugInfoToPredecessor(TII, MBB, *PredBB); 0
1321 } 0
1322 ----
1323 bool BranchFolder::OptimizeBlock(MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
1324 bool MadeChange = false; 0
1325 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent(); 0
1326 ReoptimizeBlock: 0
1327 ----
1328 MachineFunction::iterator FallThrough = MBB->getIterator(); 0
1329 ++FallThrough; 0
1330 ----
1331 // Make sure MBB and FallThrough belong to the same EH scope. ----
1332 bool SameEHScope = true; 0
1333 if (!EHScopeMembership.empty() && FallThrough != MF.end()) { 0
1334 auto MBBEHScope = EHScopeMembership.find(MBB); 0
1335 assert(MBBEHScope != EHScopeMembership.end()); 0
1336 auto FallThroughEHScope = EHScopeMembership.find(&*FallThrough); 0
1337 assert(FallThroughEHScope != EHScopeMembership.end()); 0
1338 SameEHScope = MBBEHScope->second == FallThroughEHScope->second; 0
1339 } ----
1340 ----
1341 // Analyze the branch in the current block. As a side-effect, this may cause ----
1342 // the block to become empty. ----
1343 MachineBasicBlock *CurTBB = nullptr, *CurFBB = nullptr; 0
1344 SmallVector CurCond; 0
1345 bool CurUnAnalyzable = ----
1346 TII->analyzeBranch(*MBB, CurTBB, CurFBB, CurCond, true); 0
1347 ----
1348 // If this block is empty, make everyone use its fall-through, not the block ----
1349 // explicitly. Landing pads should not do this since the landing-pad table ----
1350 // points to this block. Blocks with their addresses taken shouldn't be ----
1351 // optimized away. ----
1352 if (IsEmptyBlock(MBB) && !MBB->isEHPad() && !MBB->hasAddressTaken() && 0
1353 SameEHScope) { ----
1354 salvageDebugInfoFromEmptyBlock(TII, *MBB); 0
1355 // Dead block? Leave for cleanup later. ----
1356 if (MBB->pred_empty()) return MadeChange; 0
1357 ----
1358 if (FallThrough == MF.end()) { 0
1359 // TODO: Simplify preds to not branch here if possible! ----
1360 } else if (FallThrough->isEHPad()) { 0
1361 // Don't rewrite to a landing pad fallthough. That could lead to the case ----
1362 // where a BB jumps to more than one landing pad. ----
1363 // TODO: Is it ever worth rewriting predecessors which don't already ----
1364 // jump to a landing pad, and so can safely jump to the fallthrough? ----
1365 } else if (MBB->isSuccessor(&*FallThrough)) { 0
1366 // Rewrite all predecessors of the old block to go to the fallthrough ----
1367 // instead. ----
1368 while (!MBB->pred_empty()) { 0
1369 MachineBasicBlock *Pred = *(MBB->pred_end()-1); 0
1370 Pred->ReplaceUsesOfBlockWith(MBB, &*FallThrough); 0
1371 } ----
1372 // If MBB was the target of a jump table, update jump tables to go to the ----
1373 // fallthrough instead. ----
1374 if (MachineJumpTableInfo *MJTI = MF.getJumpTableInfo()) 0
1375 MJTI->ReplaceMBBInJumpTables(MBB, &*FallThrough); 0
1376 MadeChange = true; 0
1377 } ----
1378 return MadeChange; 0
1379 } ----
1380 ----
1381 // Check to see if we can simplify the terminator of the block before this ----
1382 // one. ----
1383 MachineBasicBlock &PrevBB = *std::prev(MachineFunction::iterator(MBB)); 0
1384 ----
1385 MachineBasicBlock *PriorTBB = nullptr, *PriorFBB = nullptr; 0
1386 SmallVector PriorCond; 0
1387 bool PriorUnAnalyzable = ----
1388 TII->analyzeBranch(PrevBB, PriorTBB, PriorFBB, PriorCond, true); 0
1389 if (!PriorUnAnalyzable) { 0
1390 // If the previous branch is conditional and both conditions go to the same ----
1391 // destination, remove the branch, replacing it with an unconditional one or ----
1392 // a fall-through. ----
1393 if (PriorTBB && PriorTBB == PriorFBB) { 0
1394 DebugLoc dl = getBranchDebugLoc(PrevBB); 0
1395 TII->removeBranch(PrevBB); 0
1396 PriorCond.clear(); 0
1397 if (PriorTBB != MBB) 0
1398 TII->insertBranch(PrevBB, PriorTBB, nullptr, PriorCond, dl); 0
1399 MadeChange = true; 0
1400 ++NumBranchOpts; 0
1401 goto ReoptimizeBlock; 0
1402 } 0
1403 ----
1404 // If the previous block unconditionally falls through to this block and ----
1405 // this block has no other predecessors, move the contents of this block ----
1406 // into the prior block. This doesn't usually happen when SimplifyCFG ----
1407 // has been used, but it can happen if tail merging splits a fall-through ----
1408 // predecessor of a block. ----
1409 // This has to check PrevBB->succ_size() because EH edges are ignored by ----
1410 // analyzeBranch. ----
1411 if (PriorCond.empty() && !PriorTBB && MBB->pred_size() == 1 && 0
1412 PrevBB.succ_size() == 1 && 0
1413 !MBB->hasAddressTaken() && !MBB->isEHPad()) { 0
1414 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nMerging into block: " << PrevBB 0
1415 << "From MBB: " << *MBB); ----
1416 // Remove redundant DBG_VALUEs first. ----
1417 if (!PrevBB.empty()) { 0
1418 MachineBasicBlock::iterator PrevBBIter = PrevBB.end(); 0
1419 --PrevBBIter; 0
1420 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBIter = MBB->begin(); 0
1421 // Check if DBG_VALUE at the end of PrevBB is identical to the ----
1422 // DBG_VALUE at the beginning of MBB. ----
1423 while (PrevBBIter != PrevBB.begin() && MBBIter != MBB->end() 0
1424 && PrevBBIter->isDebugInstr() && MBBIter->isDebugInstr()) { 0
1425 if (!MBBIter->isIdenticalTo(*PrevBBIter)) 0
1426 break; 0
1427 MachineInstr &DuplicateDbg = *MBBIter; 0
1428 ++MBBIter; -- PrevBBIter; 0
1429 DuplicateDbg.eraseFromParent(); 0
1430 } ----
1431 } ----
1432 PrevBB.splice(PrevBB.end(), MBB, MBB->begin(), MBB->end()); 0
1433 PrevBB.removeSuccessor(PrevBB.succ_begin()); 0
1434 assert(PrevBB.succ_empty()); 0
1435 PrevBB.transferSuccessors(MBB); 0
1436 MadeChange = true; 0
1437 return MadeChange; 0
1438 } ----
1439 ----
1440 // If the previous branch *only* branches to *this* block (conditional or ----
1441 // not) remove the branch. ----
1442 if (PriorTBB == MBB && !PriorFBB) { 0
1443 TII->removeBranch(PrevBB); 0
1444 MadeChange = true; 0
1445 ++NumBranchOpts; 0
1446 goto ReoptimizeBlock; 0
1447 } ----
1448 ----
1449 // If the prior block branches somewhere else on the condition and here if ----
1450 // the condition is false, remove the uncond second branch. ----
1451 if (PriorFBB == MBB) { 0
1452 DebugLoc dl = getBranchDebugLoc(PrevBB); 0
1453 TII->removeBranch(PrevBB); 0
1454 TII->insertBranch(PrevBB, PriorTBB, nullptr, PriorCond, dl); 0
1455 MadeChange = true; 0
1456 ++NumBranchOpts; 0
1457 goto ReoptimizeBlock; 0
1458 } 0
1459 ----
1460 // If the prior block branches here on true and somewhere else on false, and ----
1461 // if the branch condition is reversible, reverse the branch to create a ----
1462 // fall-through. ----
1463 if (PriorTBB == MBB) { 0
1464 SmallVector NewPriorCond(PriorCond); 0
1465 if (!TII->reverseBranchCondition(NewPriorCond)) { 0
1466 DebugLoc dl = getBranchDebugLoc(PrevBB); 0
1467 TII->removeBranch(PrevBB); 0
1468 TII->insertBranch(PrevBB, PriorFBB, nullptr, NewPriorCond, dl); 0
1469 MadeChange = true; 0
1470 ++NumBranchOpts; 0
1471 goto ReoptimizeBlock; 0
1472 } 0
1473 } 0
1474 ----
1475 // If this block has no successors (e.g. it is a return block or ends with ----
1476 // a call to a no-return function like abort or __cxa_throw) and if the pred ----
1477 // falls through into this block, and if it would otherwise fall through ----
1478 // into the block after this, move this block to the end of the function. ----
1479 // ----
1480 // We consider it more likely that execution will stay in the function (e.g. ----
1481 // due to loops) than it is to exit it. This asserts in loops etc, moving ----
1482 // the assert condition out of the loop body. ----
1483 if (MBB->succ_empty() && !PriorCond.empty() && !PriorFBB && 0
1484 MachineFunction::iterator(PriorTBB) == FallThrough && 0
1485 !MBB->canFallThrough()) { 0
1486 bool DoTransform = true; 0
1487 ----
1488 // We have to be careful that the succs of PredBB aren't both no-successor ----
1489 // blocks. If neither have successors and if PredBB is the second from ----
1490 // last block in the function, we'd just keep swapping the two blocks for ----
1491 // last. Only do the swap if one is clearly better to fall through than ----
1492 // the other. ----
1493 if (FallThrough == --MF.end() && 0
1494 !IsBetterFallthrough(PriorTBB, MBB)) 0
1495 DoTransform = false; 0
1496 ----
1497 if (DoTransform) { 0
1498 // Reverse the branch so we will fall through on the previous true cond. ----
1499 SmallVector NewPriorCond(PriorCond); 0
1500 if (!TII->reverseBranchCondition(NewPriorCond)) { 0
1501 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nMoving MBB: " << *MBB 0
1502 << "To make fallthrough to: " << *PriorTBB << "\n"); ----
1503 ----
1504 DebugLoc dl = getBranchDebugLoc(PrevBB); 0
1505 TII->removeBranch(PrevBB); 0
1506 TII->insertBranch(PrevBB, MBB, nullptr, NewPriorCond, dl); 0
1507 ----
1508 // Move this block to the end of the function. ----
1509 MBB->moveAfter(&MF.back()); 0
1510 MadeChange = true; 0
1511 ++NumBranchOpts; 0
1512 return MadeChange; 0
1513 } 0
1514 } 0
1515 } ----
1516 } ----
1517 ----
1518 if (!IsEmptyBlock(MBB)) { 0
1519 MachineInstr &TailCall = *MBB->getFirstNonDebugInstr(); 0
1520 if (TII->isUnconditionalTailCall(TailCall)) { 0
1521 SmallVector PredsChanged; 0
1522 for (auto &Pred : MBB->predecessors()) { 0
1523 MachineBasicBlock *PredTBB = nullptr, *PredFBB = nullptr; 0
1524 SmallVector PredCond; 0
1525 bool PredAnalyzable = ----
1526 !TII->analyzeBranch(*Pred, PredTBB, PredFBB, PredCond, true); 0
1527 ----
1528 // Only eliminate if MBB == TBB (Taken Basic Block) ----
1529 if (PredAnalyzable && !PredCond.empty() && PredTBB == MBB && 0
1530 PredTBB != PredFBB) { 0
1531 // The predecessor has a conditional branch to this block which ----
1532 // consists of only a tail call. Try to fold the tail call into the ----
1533 // conditional branch. ----
1534 if (TII->canMakeTailCallConditional(PredCond, TailCall)) { 0
1535 // TODO: It would be nice if analyzeBranch() could provide a pointer ----
1536 // to the branch instruction so replaceBranchWithTailCall() doesn't ----
1537 // have to search for it. ----
1538 TII->replaceBranchWithTailCall(*Pred, PredCond, TailCall); 0
1539 PredsChanged.push_back(Pred); 0
1540 } ----
1541 } ----
1542 // If the predecessor is falling through to this block, we could reverse ----
1543 // the branch condition and fold the tail call into that. However, after ----
1544 // that we might have to re-arrange the CFG to fall through to the other ----
1545 // block and there is a high risk of regressing code size rather than ----
1546 // improving it. ----
1547 } 0
1548 if (!PredsChanged.empty()) { 0
1549 NumTailCalls += PredsChanged.size(); 0
1550 for (auto &Pred : PredsChanged) 0
1551 Pred->removeSuccessor(MBB); 0
1552 ----
1553 return true; 0
1554 } ----
1555 } 0
1556 } ----
1557 ----
1558 if (!CurUnAnalyzable) { 0
1559 // If this is a two-way branch, and the FBB branches to this block, reverse ----
1560 // the condition so the single-basic-block loop is faster. Instead of: ----
1561 // Loop: xxx; jcc Out; jmp Loop ----
1562 // we want: ----
1563 // Loop: xxx; jncc Loop; jmp Out ----
1564 if (CurTBB && CurFBB && CurFBB == MBB && CurTBB != MBB) { 0
1565 SmallVector NewCond(CurCond); 0
1566 if (!TII->reverseBranchCondition(NewCond)) { 0
1567 DebugLoc dl = getBranchDebugLoc(*MBB); 0
1568 TII->removeBranch(*MBB); 0
1569 TII->insertBranch(*MBB, CurFBB, CurTBB, NewCond, dl); 0
1570 MadeChange = true; 0
1571 ++NumBranchOpts; 0
1572 goto ReoptimizeBlock; 0
1573 } 0
1574 } 0
1575 ----
1576 // If this branch is the only thing in its block, see if we can forward ----
1577 // other blocks across it. ----
1578 if (CurTBB && CurCond.empty() && !CurFBB && 0
1579 IsBranchOnlyBlock(MBB) && CurTBB != MBB && 0
1580 !MBB->hasAddressTaken() && !MBB->isEHPad()) { 0
1581 DebugLoc dl = getBranchDebugLoc(*MBB); 0
1582 // This block may contain just an unconditional branch. Because there can ----
1583 // be 'non-branch terminators' in the block, try removing the branch and ----
1584 // then seeing if the block is empty. ----
1585 TII->removeBranch(*MBB); 0
1586 // If the only things remaining in the block are debug info, remove these ----
1587 // as well, so this will behave the same as an empty block in non-debug ----
1588 // mode. ----
1589 if (IsEmptyBlock(MBB)) { 0
1590 // Make the block empty, losing the debug info (we could probably ----
1591 // improve this in some cases.) ----
1592 MBB->erase(MBB->begin(), MBB->end()); 0
1593 } ----
1594 // If this block is just an unconditional branch to CurTBB, we can ----
1595 // usually completely eliminate the block. The only case we cannot ----
1596 // completely eliminate the block is when the block before this one ----
1597 // falls through into MBB and we can't understand the prior block's branch ----
1598 // condition. ----
1599 if (MBB->empty()) { 0
1600 bool PredHasNoFallThrough = !PrevBB.canFallThrough(); 0
1601 if (PredHasNoFallThrough || !PriorUnAnalyzable || 0
1602 !PrevBB.isSuccessor(MBB)) { 0
1603 // If the prior block falls through into us, turn it into an ----
1604 // explicit branch to us to make updates simpler. ----
1605 if (!PredHasNoFallThrough && PrevBB.isSuccessor(MBB) && 0
1606 PriorTBB != MBB && PriorFBB != MBB) { 0
1607 if (!PriorTBB) { 0
1608 assert(PriorCond.empty() && !PriorFBB && 0
1609 "Bad branch analysis"); ----
1610 PriorTBB = MBB; 0
1611 } else { ----
1612 assert(!PriorFBB && "Machine CFG out of date!"); 0
1613 PriorFBB = MBB; 0
1614 } ----
1615 DebugLoc pdl = getBranchDebugLoc(PrevBB); 0
1616 TII->removeBranch(PrevBB); 0
1617 TII->insertBranch(PrevBB, PriorTBB, PriorFBB, PriorCond, pdl); 0
1618 } 0
1619 ----
1620 // Iterate through all the predecessors, revectoring each in-turn. ----
1621 size_t PI = 0; 0
1622 bool DidChange = false; 0
1623 bool HasBranchToSelf = false; 0
1624 while(PI != MBB->pred_size()) { 0
1625 MachineBasicBlock *PMBB = *(MBB->pred_begin() + PI); 0
1626 if (PMBB == MBB) { 0
1627 // If this block has an uncond branch to itself, leave it. ----
1628 ++PI; 0
1629 HasBranchToSelf = true; 0
1630 } else { ----
1631 DidChange = true; 0
1632 PMBB->ReplaceUsesOfBlockWith(MBB, CurTBB); 0
1633 // If this change resulted in PMBB ending in a conditional ----
1634 // branch where both conditions go to the same destination, ----
1635 // change this to an unconditional branch. ----
1636 MachineBasicBlock *NewCurTBB = nullptr, *NewCurFBB = nullptr; 0
1637 SmallVector NewCurCond; 0
1638 bool NewCurUnAnalyzable = TII->analyzeBranch( 0
1639 *PMBB, NewCurTBB, NewCurFBB, NewCurCond, true); ----
1640 if (!NewCurUnAnalyzable && NewCurTBB && NewCurTBB == NewCurFBB) { 0
1641 DebugLoc pdl = getBranchDebugLoc(*PMBB); 0
1642 TII->removeBranch(*PMBB); 0
1643 NewCurCond.clear(); 0
1644 TII->insertBranch(*PMBB, NewCurTBB, nullptr, NewCurCond, pdl); 0
1645 MadeChange = true; 0
1646 ++NumBranchOpts; 0
1647 } 0
1648 } 0
1649 } ----
1650 ----
1651 // Change any jumptables to go to the new MBB. ----
1652 if (MachineJumpTableInfo *MJTI = MF.getJumpTableInfo()) 0
1653 MJTI->ReplaceMBBInJumpTables(MBB, CurTBB); 0
1654 if (DidChange) { 0
1655 ++NumBranchOpts; 0
1656 MadeChange = true; 0
1657 if (!HasBranchToSelf) return MadeChange; 0
1658 } ----
1659 } ----
1660 } ----
1661 ----
1662 // Add the branch back if the block is more than just an uncond branch. ----
1663 TII->insertBranch(*MBB, CurTBB, nullptr, CurCond, dl); 0
1664 } 0
1665 } ----
1666 ----
1667 // If the prior block doesn't fall through into this block, and if this ----
1668 // block doesn't fall through into some other block, see if we can find a ----
1669 // place to move this block where a fall-through will happen. ----
1670 if (!PrevBB.canFallThrough()) { 0
1671 // Now we know that there was no fall-through into this block, check to ----
1672 // see if it has a fall-through into its successor. ----
1673 bool CurFallsThru = MBB->canFallThrough(); 0
1674 ----
1675 if (!MBB->isEHPad()) { 0
1676 // Check all the predecessors of this block. If one of them has no fall ----
1677 // throughs, and analyzeBranch thinks it _could_ fallthrough to this ----
1678 // block, move this block right after it. ----
1679 for (MachineBasicBlock *PredBB : MBB->predecessors()) { 0
1680 // Analyze the branch at the end of the pred. ----
1681 MachineBasicBlock *PredTBB = nullptr, *PredFBB = nullptr; 0
1682 SmallVector PredCond; 0
1683 if (PredBB != MBB && !PredBB->canFallThrough() && 0
1684 !TII->analyzeBranch(*PredBB, PredTBB, PredFBB, PredCond, true) && 0
1685 (PredTBB == MBB || PredFBB == MBB) && 0
1686 (!CurFallsThru || !CurTBB || !CurFBB) && 0
1687 (!CurFallsThru || MBB->getNumber() >= PredBB->getNumber())) { 0
1688 // If the current block doesn't fall through, just move it. ----
1689 // If the current block can fall through and does not end with a ----
1690 // conditional branch, we need to append an unconditional jump to ----
1691 // the (current) next block. To avoid a possible compile-time ----
1692 // infinite loop, move blocks only backward in this case. ----
1693 // Also, if there are already 2 branches here, we cannot add a third; ----
1694 // this means we have the case ----
1695 // Bcc next ----
1696 // B elsewhere ----
1697 // next: ----
1698 if (CurFallsThru) { 0
1699 MachineBasicBlock *NextBB = &*std::next(MBB->getIterator()); 0
1700 CurCond.clear(); 0
1701 TII->insertBranch(*MBB, NextBB, nullptr, CurCond, DebugLoc()); 0
1702 } ----
1703 MBB->moveAfter(PredBB); 0
1704 MadeChange = true; 0
1705 goto ReoptimizeBlock; 0
1706 } ----
1707 } 0
1708 } ----
1709 ----
1710 if (!CurFallsThru) { 0
1711 // Check analyzable branch-successors to see if we can move this block ----
1712 // before one. ----
1713 if (!CurUnAnalyzable) { 0
1714 for (MachineBasicBlock *SuccBB : {CurFBB, CurTBB}) { 0
1715 if (!SuccBB) 0
1716 continue; 0
1717 // Analyze the branch at the end of the block before the succ. ----
1718 MachineFunction::iterator SuccPrev = --SuccBB->getIterator(); 0
1719 ----
1720 // If this block doesn't already fall-through to that successor, and ----
1721 // if the succ doesn't already have a block that can fall through into ----
1722 // it, we can arrange for the fallthrough to happen. ----
1723 if (SuccBB != MBB && &*SuccPrev != MBB && 0
1724 !SuccPrev->canFallThrough()) { 0
1725 MBB->moveBefore(SuccBB); 0
1726 MadeChange = true; 0
1727 goto ReoptimizeBlock; 0
1728 } ----
1729 } ----
1730 } ----
1731 ----
1732 // Okay, there is no really great place to put this block. If, however, ----
1733 // the block before this one would be a fall-through if this block were ----
1734 // removed, move this block to the end of the function. There is no real ----
1735 // advantage in "falling through" to an EH block, so we don't want to ----
1736 // perform this transformation for that case. ----
1737 // ----
1738 // Also, Windows EH introduced the possibility of an arbitrary number of ----
1739 // successors to a given block. The analyzeBranch call does not consider ----
1740 // exception handling and so we can get in a state where a block ----
1741 // containing a call is followed by multiple EH blocks that would be ----
1742 // rotated infinitely at the end of the function if the transformation ----
1743 // below were performed for EH "FallThrough" blocks. Therefore, even if ----
1744 // that appears not to be happening anymore, we should assume that it is ----
1745 // possible and not remove the "!FallThrough()->isEHPad" condition below. ----
1746 MachineBasicBlock *PrevTBB = nullptr, *PrevFBB = nullptr; 0
1747 SmallVector PrevCond; 0
1748 if (FallThrough != MF.end() && 0
1749 !FallThrough->isEHPad() && 0
1750 !TII->analyzeBranch(PrevBB, PrevTBB, PrevFBB, PrevCond, true) && 0
1751 PrevBB.isSuccessor(&*FallThrough)) { 0
1752 MBB->moveAfter(&MF.back()); 0
1753 MadeChange = true; 0
1754 return MadeChange; 0
1755 } ----
1756 } 0
1757 } ----
1758 ----
1759 return MadeChange; 0
1760 } ----
1761 ----
1762 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
1763 // Hoist Common Code ----
1764 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----

1766 bool BranchFolder::HoistCommonCode(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
1767 bool MadeChange = false; 0
1768 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : llvm::make_early_inc_range(MF)) 0
1769 MadeChange |= HoistCommonCodeInSuccs(&MBB); 0
1770 ----
1771 return MadeChange; 0
1772 } ----

1774 /// findFalseBlock - BB has a fallthrough. Find its 'false' successor given ----
1775 /// its 'true' successor. ----
1776 static MachineBasicBlock *findFalseBlock(MachineBasicBlock *BB, 0
1777 MachineBasicBlock *TrueBB) { ----
1778 for (MachineBasicBlock *SuccBB : BB->successors()) 0
1779 if (SuccBB != TrueBB) 0
1780 return SuccBB; 0
1781 return nullptr; 0
1782 } ----

1785 static void addRegAndItsAliases(Register Reg, const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI, 0
1786 Container &Set) { ----
1787 if (Reg.isPhysical()) { 0
1788 for (MCRegAliasIterator AI(Reg, TRI, true); AI.isValid(); ++AI) 0

1790 } else { ----
1791 Set.insert(Reg); 0

1795 /// findHoistingInsertPosAndDeps - Find the location to move common instructions ----
1796 /// in successors to. The location is usually just before the terminator, ----
1797 /// however if the terminator is a conditional branch and its previous ----
1798 /// instruction is the flag setting instruction, the previous instruction is ----
1799 /// the preferred location. This function also gathers uses and defs of the ----
1800 /// instructions from the insertion point to the end of the block. The data is ----
1801 /// used by HoistCommonCodeInSuccs to ensure safety. ----
1802 static ----
1803 MachineBasicBlock::iterator findHoistingInsertPosAndDeps(MachineBasicBlock *MBB, 0
1804 const TargetInstrInfo *TII, ----
1805 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI, ----
1806 SmallSet &Uses, ----
1807 SmallSet &Defs) { ----
1808 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Loc = MBB->getFirstTerminator(); 0
1809 if (!TII->isUnpredicatedTerminator(*Loc)) 0
1810 return MBB->end(); 0
1811 ----
1812 for (const MachineOperand &MO : Loc->operands()) { 0
1813 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
1814 continue; 0
1815 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1816 if (!Reg) 0
1817 continue; 0
1818 if (MO.isUse()) { 0
1819 addRegAndItsAliases(Reg, TRI, Uses); 0
1820 } else { ----
1821 if (!MO.isDead()) 0
1822 // Don't try to hoist code in the rare case the terminator defines a ----
1823 // register that is later used. ----
1824 return MBB->end(); 0
1825 ----
1826 // If the terminator defines a register, make sure we don't hoist ----
1827 // the instruction whose def might be clobbered by the terminator. ----
1828 addRegAndItsAliases(Reg, TRI, Defs); 0
1829 } ----
1830 } ----
1831 ----
1832 if (Uses.empty()) 0
1833 return Loc; 0
1834 // If the terminator is the only instruction in the block and Uses is not ----
1835 // empty (or we would have returned above), we can still safely hoist ----
1836 // instructions just before the terminator as long as the Defs/Uses are not ----
1837 // violated (which is checked in HoistCommonCodeInSuccs). ----
1838 if (Loc == MBB->begin()) 0
1839 return Loc; 0
1840 ----
1841 // The terminator is probably a conditional branch, try not to separate the ----
1842 // branch from condition setting instruction. ----
1843 MachineBasicBlock::iterator PI = prev_nodbg(Loc, MBB->begin()); 0
1844 ----
1845 bool IsDef = false; 0
1846 for (const MachineOperand &MO : PI->operands()) { 0
1847 // If PI has a regmask operand, it is probably a call. Separate away. ----
1848 if (MO.isRegMask()) 0
1849 return Loc; 0
1850 if (!MO.isReg() || MO.isUse()) 0
1851 continue; 0
1852 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1853 if (!Reg) 0
1854 continue; 0
1855 if (Uses.count(Reg)) { 0
1856 IsDef = true; 0
1857 break; 0
1858 } ----
1859 } ----
1860 if (!IsDef) 0
1861 // The condition setting instruction is not just before the conditional ----
1862 // branch. ----
1863 return Loc; 0
1864 ----
1865 // Be conservative, don't insert instruction above something that may have ----
1866 // side-effects. And since it's potentially bad to separate flag setting ----
1867 // instruction from the conditional branch, just abort the optimization ----
1868 // completely. ----
1869 // Also avoid moving code above predicated instruction since it's hard to ----
1870 // reason about register liveness with predicated instruction. ----
1871 bool DontMoveAcrossStore = true; 0
1872 if (!PI->isSafeToMove(nullptr, DontMoveAcrossStore) || TII->isPredicated(*PI)) 0
1873 return MBB->end(); 0
1874 ----
1875 // Find out what registers are live. Note this routine is ignoring other live ----
1876 // registers which are only used by instructions in successor blocks. ----
1877 for (const MachineOperand &MO : PI->operands()) { 0
1878 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
1879 continue; 0
1880 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1881 if (!Reg) 0
1882 continue; 0
1883 if (MO.isUse()) { 0
1884 addRegAndItsAliases(Reg, TRI, Uses); 0
1885 } else { ----
1886 if (Uses.erase(Reg)) { 0
1887 if (Reg.isPhysical()) { 0
1888 for (MCPhysReg SubReg : TRI->subregs(Reg)) 0
1889 Uses.erase(SubReg); // Use sub-registers to be conservative 0
1890 } ----
1891 } ----
1892 addRegAndItsAliases(Reg, TRI, Defs); 0
1893 } ----
1894 } ----
1895 ----
1896 return PI; 0
1897 } ----
1898 ----
1899 bool BranchFolder::HoistCommonCodeInSuccs(MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
1900 MachineBasicBlock *TBB = nullptr, *FBB = nullptr; 0
1901 SmallVector Cond; 0
1902 if (TII->analyzeBranch(*MBB, TBB, FBB, Cond, true) || !TBB || Cond.empty()) 0
1903 return false; 0
1904 ----
1905 if (!FBB) FBB = findFalseBlock(MBB, TBB); 0
1906 if (!FBB) 0
1907 // Malformed bcc? True and false blocks are the same? ----
1908 return false; 0
1909 ----
1910 // Restrict the optimization to cases where MBB is the only predecessor, ----
1911 // it is an obvious win. ----
1912 if (TBB->pred_size() > 1 || FBB->pred_size() > 1) 0
1913 return false; 0
1914 ----
1915 // Find a suitable position to hoist the common instructions to. Also figure ----
1916 // out which registers are used or defined by instructions from the insertion ----
1917 // point to the end of the block. ----
1918 SmallSet Uses, Defs; 0
1919 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Loc = ----
1920 findHoistingInsertPosAndDeps(MBB, TII, TRI, Uses, Defs); 0
1921 if (Loc == MBB->end()) 0
1922 return false; 0
1923 ----
1924 bool HasDups = false; 0
1925 SmallSet ActiveDefsSet, AllDefsSet; 0
1926 MachineBasicBlock::iterator TIB = TBB->begin(); 0
1927 MachineBasicBlock::iterator FIB = FBB->begin(); 0
1928 MachineBasicBlock::iterator TIE = TBB->end(); 0
1929 MachineBasicBlock::iterator FIE = FBB->end(); 0
1930 while (TIB != TIE && FIB != FIE) { 0
1931 // Skip dbg_value instructions. These do not count. ----
1932 TIB = skipDebugInstructionsForward(TIB, TIE, false); 0
1933 FIB = skipDebugInstructionsForward(FIB, FIE, false); 0
1934 if (TIB == TIE || FIB == FIE) 0
1935 break; 0
1936 ----
1937 if (!TIB->isIdenticalTo(*FIB, MachineInstr::CheckKillDead)) 0
1938 break; 0
1939 ----
1940 if (TII->isPredicated(*TIB)) 0
1941 // Hard to reason about register liveness with predicated instruction. ----
1942 break; 0
1943 ----
1944 bool IsSafe = true; 0
1945 for (MachineOperand &MO : TIB->operands()) { 0
1946 // Don't attempt to hoist instructions with register masks. ----
1947 if (MO.isRegMask()) { 0
1948 IsSafe = false; 0
1949 break; 0
1950 } ----
1951 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
1952 continue; 0
1953 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1954 if (!Reg) 0
1955 continue; 0
1956 if (MO.isDef()) { 0
1957 if (Uses.count(Reg)) { 0
1958 // Avoid clobbering a register that's used by the instruction at ----
1959 // the point of insertion. ----
1960 IsSafe = false; 0
1961 break; 0
1962 } ----
1963 ----
1964 if (Defs.count(Reg) && !MO.isDead()) { 0
1965 // Don't hoist the instruction if the def would be clobber by the ----
1966 // instruction at the point insertion. FIXME: This is overly ----
1967 // conservative. It should be possible to hoist the instructions ----
1968 // in BB2 in the following example: ----
1969 // BB1: ----
1970 // r1, eflag = op1 r2, r3 ----
1971 // brcc eflag ----
1972 // ----
1973 // BB2: ----
1974 // r1 = op2, ... ----
1975 // = op3, killed r1 ----
1976 IsSafe = false; 0
1977 break; 0
1978 } ----
1979 } else if (!ActiveDefsSet.count(Reg)) { 0
1980 if (Defs.count(Reg)) { 0
1981 // Use is defined by the instruction at the point of insertion. ----
1982 IsSafe = false; 0
1983 break; 0
1984 } ----
1985 ----
1986 if (MO.isKill() && Uses.count(Reg)) 0
1987 // Kills a register that's read by the instruction at the point of ----
1988 // insertion. Remove the kill marker. ----
1989 MO.setIsKill(false); 0
1990 } ----
1991 } ----
1992 if (!IsSafe) 0
1993 break; 0
1994 ----
1995 bool DontMoveAcrossStore = true; 0
1996 if (!TIB->isSafeToMove(nullptr, DontMoveAcrossStore)) 0
1997 break; 0
1998 ----
1999 // Remove kills from ActiveDefsSet, these registers had short live ranges. ----
2000 for (const MachineOperand &MO : TIB->all_uses()) { 0
2001 if (!MO.isKill()) 0
2002 continue; 0
2003 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
2004 if (!Reg) 0
2005 continue; 0
2006 if (!AllDefsSet.count(Reg)) { 0
2007 continue; 0
2008 } ----
2009 if (Reg.isPhysical()) { 0
2010 for (MCRegAliasIterator AI(Reg, TRI, true); AI.isValid(); ++AI) 0
2011 ActiveDefsSet.erase(*AI); 0
2012 } else { ----
2013 ActiveDefsSet.erase(Reg); 0
2014 } ----
2015 } ----
2016 ----
2017 // Track local defs so we can update liveins. ----
2018 for (const MachineOperand &MO : TIB->all_defs()) { 0
2019 if (MO.isDead()) 0
2020 continue; 0
2021 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
2022 if (!Reg || Reg.isVirtual()) 0
2023 continue; 0
2024 addRegAndItsAliases(Reg, TRI, ActiveDefsSet); 0
2025 addRegAndItsAliases(Reg, TRI, AllDefsSet); 0
2026 } ----
2027 ----
2028 HasDups = true; 0
2029 ++TIB; 0
2030 ++FIB; 0
2031 } ----
2032 ----
2033 if (!HasDups) 0
2034 return false; 0
2035 ----
2036 MBB->splice(Loc, TBB, TBB->begin(), TIB); 0
2037 FBB->erase(FBB->begin(), FIB); 0
2038 ----
2039 if (UpdateLiveIns) { 0
2040 recomputeLiveIns(*TBB); 0
2041 recomputeLiveIns(*FBB); 0
2042 } ----
2043 ----
2044 ++NumHoist; 0
2045 return true; 0
2046 } 0
